title: Internazionale vs Feyenoord - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Round of 16 - 2nd Leg
description: Internazionale and Feyenoord have met on three previous occasions in Europe, with both sides winning one game each. Those two victories have both been achieved by the away side, with Feyenoord winning in Italy in April 2002 and Internazionale winning in the Netherlands last week. Feyenoord are winless in their last eight away matches against Italian sides in European competition, and haven’t managed to win any of their 12 overall matches there by more than a single goal.

title: Olympiakos Piraeus vs Bodø / Glimt - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - R16 - 2nd Leg
description: Olympiakos have won just one of their seven major European meetings with Norwegian clubs, with that one win coming at home to Molde in September 1999 in the UEFA Champions League. Norwegian clubs have lost each of their last four away European matches in Greece, with Vålerenga the last club from Norway to win there in a UEFA Europa League qualifier in August 2009 at PAOK Salonika.

title: Lazio vs Viktoria Plzeň - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - R16 - 2nd Leg
description: Lazio have only hosted a Czechia side once in a knockout match in major European competition, losing 3-0 against Sparta Prague in the UEFA Europa League in March 2016. Viktoria Plzen have lost five of their six away European matches in Italy – including the last four in a row – with their one win coming in a 3-0 success at Napoli in February 2013 in the UEFA Europa League.

title: Bayer Leverkusen vs Bayern Munchen - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Round of 16 - 2nd Leg
description: Following their 3-0 victory in the first leg, Bayern Munich could register multiple wins over Bayer Leverkusen in the same campaign for the first time since 2020-21. Bayer Leverkusen are unbeaten in their three home games against Bayern Munich under Xabi Alonso, winning two of them. Prior to Alonso’s arrival, they only won one of their previous eight home matches against Bayern, between 2015-16 and 2021-22.

title: Liverpool vs PSG - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Round of 16 - 2nd Leg
description: After losing their first European meeting with Paris SG in April 1997, Liverpool have only lost one of four against them since, winning three of them. None of the last 15 French sides to play away from home against an English opponent in Europe have managed to win, with 14 of those ending in defeats. Indeed, the last such victory was by Paris SG in December 2020 against Manchester United.

title: Manchester United vs Real Sociedad - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - R16 - 2nd Leg
description: There have only been nine goals scored in seven European meetings between Man Utd and Real Sociedad, with four of those coming in the same game by the Red Devils in a 4-0 win in February 2021. Three of Real Sociedad’s four away European games in England have come at Old Trafford against Man Utd, with their other a 6-0 loss at Liverpool in November 1975.

title: Olympique Lyonnais vs FCSB - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - R16 - 2nd Leg
description: Lyon are unbeaten in all five of their major European matches against FCSB. They have only faced Sparta Prague more often without losing. FCSB have never won a major away European match in France in six attempts, with this their first visit since losing 2-0 to Lyon in November 2008 in the UEFA Champions League.

title: Lille vs Borussia Dortmund - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Round of 16 - 2nd Leg
description: Lille have only won one of their 10 major European meetings with German clubs, beating VfL Wolfsburg 3-1 in December 2021 in the UEFA Champions League. All three of their games with Borussia Dortmund have ended as draws. When Borussia Dortmund have drawn the first leg of a major European knockout tie at home, they have been eliminated in six out of seven instances; the other was against Alania Vladikavkaz in the first round of the 1993-94 UEFA Cup.

title: Arsenal vs PSV - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Round of 16 - 2nd Leg
description: Arsenal’s 7-1 victory in the first leg against PSV was the biggest ever away win in the knockout stages of the UEFA Champions League. The only English team to score 10 goals across two legs in the competition was Man City vs Schalke 04 in 2018-19’s last 16. PSV are winless in their last six away major European games in England, with their last two visits defeats to Arsenal. They’ve won four of 20 away games, beating Leeds twice, Newcastle and Spurs.

title: Rangers vs Fenerbahçe - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - R16 - 2nd Leg
description: Rangers are unbeaten in their five home matches against Turkish sides in European competition, conceding only one goal in those five games in a 2-1 win over Galatasaray in October 2020. Rangers have lost just two of their last 14 home games in the UEFA Europa League, though did lose their last game in the knockout stages in March 2024 against Benfica 1-0.

title: Tottenham Hotspur vs AZ Alkmaar - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - R16 - 2nd Leg
description: Tottenham Hotspur have won four of their last five home European matches against Dutch teams, losing the other 1-0 against Ajax in April 2019 in the UEFA Champions League. AZ have lost all nine of their away European matches in England, losing to eight different teams. It is the worst 100% losing record away to English sides of any team in major European football history.

title: Atletico Madrid vs Real Madrid - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Round of 16 - 2nd Leg
description: Atletico Madrid have lost the first leg in six previous UEFA Champions League ties and have come back to progress from three of them, with all three instances coming when they’ve lost the first leg away. Real Madrid have progressed from 21 of their last 22 UEFA Champions League ties when they’ve won the first leg, with the exception against Ajax in the last 16 in 2018-19. Under Carlo Ancelotti, they’ve progressed from nine out of nine.

title: Aston Villa vs Club Brugge - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Round of 16 - 2nd Leg
description: Aston Villa last hosted a Belgian side in any European competition back in April 1982 in the European Cup semi-final against Anderlecht, winning 1-0 with a goal from Tony Morley on their way to winning the trophy. Club Brugge have never won away in England in major European competition in 14 attempts, losing their last five visits. Only Anderlecht and Dynamo Kyiv have played more in England without ever winning.

title: Bodo / Glimt vs Lazio - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Quarter Finals 1st Leg
description: This will be the first ever European meeting between Bodø/Glimt and Lazio. The Norwegian side have won their last three home European matches against Italian sides, beating Sampdoria in 1994 in the Cup Winners’ Cup and Roma twice in the 2021-22 Conference League. Lazio’s only two previous European meetings with a Norwegian side was in the 2015-16 UEFA Europa League, beating Rosenborg at home and away.

title: Olympique Lyonnais vs Manchester United - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Quarter Finals 1st Leg
description: Lyon have never beaten Manchester United in four attempts in major European competitions only facing Barcelona more often without winning in Europe. Manchester United’s two away visits to Lyon have both been in the UEFA Champions League and on both occasions they came from behind to draw, from 2-0 down to draw 2-2 in September 2004 and 1-0 down to draw 1-1 in February 2008.

title: Arsenal vs Real Madrid - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Quarter Finals - 1st Leg
description: This will be just the third meeting between Arsenal and Real Madrid in European competition, following their last 16 tie in the UEFA Champions League in 2005-06. Arsenal won 1-0 in the first leg away from home, before drawing 0-0 at Highbury in the second leg. Since the start of the 2017-18 campaign, Real Madrid have played 22 matches against English sides in the knockout stages of the UEFA Champions League. This is 10 more than any other team against sides from a specific nation in this period, after Liverpool and Manchester City’s 12 meetings each with Spanish teams.

title: Bayern Munchen vs Internazionale - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Quarter Finals - 1st Leg
description: This will be the 10th meeting between Bayern Munich and Internazionale in European competition, with the German side winning five of the previous nine, including the last time they faced each other in the UEFA Champions League. Internazionale have lost four of their seven games against Bayern Munich in the UEFA Champions League, but have eliminated them in both of their meetings in the knockout stages of the competition: 2-0 in the 2009-10 final and progressing on away goals over two legs in 2010-11 in the last 16.

title: Rangers vs Athletic Club - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Quarter Finals 1st Leg
description: Rangers and Athletic Club faced in the 1968-69 Inter-Cities Fairs Cup in the quarter-final – the Gers won 4-1 in the first leg at home, before Athletic won 2-0 in the second leg, with the Scottish side going through 4-3 on aggregate. Athletic Club have lost both of their major European visits to Scotland, losing 1-0 to Dunfermline Athletic in 1965 and 4-1 to Rangers in 1969, both in the Inter-Cities Fairs Cup.

title: Tottenham Hotspur vs Eintracht Frankfurt - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Quarter Finals 1st Leg
description: Tottenham Hotspur and Eintracht Frankfurt last faced in the UEFA Champions League group stages in 2022-23, with Spurs drawing 0-0 in Germany and winning 3-2 at the Tottenham Hotspur Stadium that season. The only previous European knockout meeting between Spurs and Eintracht Frankfurt was in the 1981-82 Cup Winners’ Cup quarter-final – Spurs won 2-0 at home before losing 2-1 away in the second leg, but progressed 3-2 on aggregate.

title: PSG vs Aston Villa - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Quarter Finals - 1st Leg
description: Paris SG and Aston Villa will meet for the first time in European competition, with this just the second UEFA Champions League quarter-final between French and English sides in the last eight campaigns. Paris SG eliminated Liverpool in the last 16 of this season’s UEFA Champions League, after having exited the competition in each of their last three knockout stage meetings with English sides.

title: Barcelona vs Borussia Dortmund - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Quarter Finals - 1st Leg
description: Barcelona are unbeaten in their five meetings with Borussia Dortmund in European competition, including a victory over them earlier in this season’s UEFA Champions League. Only against Lyon, Napoli and Werder Bremen have they played more in Europe without losing. While Borussia Dortmund haven’t won any of their five games against Barcelona, they’ve only gone six consecutive European matches without beating an opponent against two other sides; one of which is another Spanish team.

title: Manchester United vs Olympique Lyonnais - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Quater Finals 2nd Leg
description: This will be the third time that Manchester United have faced Lyon in European competition at Old Trafford, with the Red Devils winning both prior meetings. Lyon have lost just one of their last nine European games against sides from England, a 3-0 defeat to West Ham during the 2021-22 UEFA Europa League.

title: Athletic Club vs Rangers - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Quater Finals 2nd Leg
description: Athletic Club have only hosted Rangers once before, beating them 2-0 in the Fairs Cup in April 1969. The only other time Athletic have hosted a Scottish club was in two games against Dunfermline in 1965, also in the Fairs Cup, winning 1-0 and then 2-1 in a deciding game. Rangers won 3-2 away at Real Betis in their last European game in Spain, having gone 13 away games without winning there beforehand between 1962 and 2018.

title: Barcelona vs Mallorca - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 33
description: Barcelona have won 15 and drawn two of their last 17 games against Mallorca in LaLiga since a 1-2 away defeat in May 2009, the best unbeaten run against the Balearic side in their entire history in the competition. Mallorca have failed to win any of their last nine away games against Barcelona in LaLiga, losing their last six, the worst run of consecutive defeats on Azulgrana soil in their top-flight history.

title: Deportivo Alaves vs Real Sociedad - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 33
description: Alaves won their last game against Real Sociedad in LaLiga and have only once won both in the same season against the San Sebastian side in the top-flight, in 2001/02 under Jose Manuel Esnal ‘Mane’. Real Sociedad have collected points on their last three visits to Alaves in LaLiga, their longest run without an away defeat against Alaves in the top-flight.

title: Real Betis vs Real Valladolid - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 33
description: Real Betis have lost four of their last nine LaLiga games against Real Valladolid after losing only one of their previous 15 against them in the competition. At home, Real Betis have won their last two LaLiga games against Real Valladolid, and have only twice recorded 3+ home wins against the Pucelanos in the top-flight: W3 in 1988 and W4 in 1999.

title: Atletico Madrid vs Rayo Vallecano - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 33
description: Atletico de Madrid have not lost any of their last 15 LaLiga matches against Rayo Vallecano, since a 1-2 defeat in Vallecas in February 2013, their longest unbeaten run against them in their history in the competition. Rayo Vallecano have only earned one point in their last 10 LaLiga away matches against Atletico de Madrid, after having picked up points in four of their first nine visits to Atletico de Madrid in the competition.

title: Celta de Vigo vs Villarreal - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 33
description: Celta Vigo have won just one of their last seven games against Villarreal in LaLiga, 3-2 in May 2024, having won four of their previous six top-flight meetings. Villarreal have collected points in 10 of their last 12 away games against Celta Vigo in LaLiga, having lost on each of their first six visits to the Galician ground in the competition.

title: Getafe vs Real Madrid - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 33
description: Getafe have lost their last six meetings with Real Madrid in LaLiga, failing to score in five of them – against Real Madrid they have suffered the most defeats in the competition and conceded the most goals. After losing in three of their first five visits to Getafe in LaLiga between 2005 and 2008, Real Madrid have only lost in two of their next 14 away games against Getafe in the top-flight.

title: Barcelona vs Mallorca - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 33
description: Barcelona have won 15 and drawn two of their last 17 games against Mallorca in LaLiga since a 1-2 away defeat in May 2009, the best unbeaten run against the Balearic side in their entire history in the competition. Mallorca have failed to win any of their last nine away games against Barcelona in LaLiga, losing their last six, the worst run of consecutive defeats on Azulgrana soil in their top-flight history.

title: Villarreal vs Osasuna - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 34
description: Villarreal have not lost any of their last five LaLiga matches against Osasuna, and could equal their best unbeaten run against the Navarrese side in the top-flight, achieved between 2001 and 2003. Osasuna have won two of their last four LaLiga away matches against Villarreal, as many wins as they had in their previous 15 away games against the Yellows in the competition.

title: Rayo Vallecano vs Getafe - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 34
description: Rayo Vallecano have only won two of their last nine LaLiga matches against Getafe, after having achieved eight wins in their previous 10 top-flight clashes beforehand. Getafe have drawn 0-0 against Rayo Vallecano in both of their last two LaLiga visits to Vallecas; only against Osasuna at El Sadar have they recorded three consecutive 0-0 draws away from home in their LaLiga history.

title: Real Madrid vs Celta de Vigo - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 34
description: Real Madrid have won 19 and drawn two of their last 21 LaLiga matches against Celta de Vigo, scoring in all 21, their longest ever unbeaten run against the Galician side and their longest current unbeaten run against any opponent in the competition. Celta de Vigo have picked up just one point from their last 12 away LaLiga matches against Real Madrid, a 2-2 draw in February 2020, and have not won at Real Madrid in the competition since November 2006 under Fernando Vázquez.

title: Sevilla vs Leganes - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 34
description: Sevilla have only won two of their last six LaLiga games against Leganes and lost 0-1 in the reverse fixture this season. They have never lost both fixtures in a single campaign against Leganes in the top-flight. At home, Sevilla have only lost one of their eight home games in all competitions against Leganes, going 0-3 in LaLiga in May 2019.

title: Las Palmas vs Valencia - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 34
description: UD Las Palmas have won six of their 12 LaLiga matches against Valencia in the 21st Century, more than against any other opponent in the competition in this period. Valencia have lost their last four away matches against UD Las Palmas in LaLiga. Only once before have the Valencian side lost more consecutive away matches against the Canary Islands in the competition.

title: Real Valladolid vs Barcelona - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 34
description: Real Valladolid have won two of their last five home matches against FC Barcelona in LaLiga, achieving the same number of victories as in their previous 17 home matches in the competition. Barcelona have won 16 of their last 18 LaLiga matches against Real Valladolid, losing the other two, both at the Jose Zorrilla. This is the Blaugranas longest run in the competition without a draw.

description: Each Ligue 1 Match week is condensed into a 52-minute highlights show. Every game, goal, penalty, red card and everything in between is squeezed into an action-packed hour to ensure no football fan misses a kick across the game season.

title: Monaco vs Olympique Marseille - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 29
description: Since returning to Ligue 1 in the summer of 2013, Monaco have scored in 21 of their 22 matches against Marseille. With 47 goals scored, OM are the opponent against whom ASM have scored the most goals against in the top-flight in this period. Marseille are the team that have won most often away to Monaco in Ligue 1, winning four of the six most recent meetings.

title: Strasbourg vs Nice - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 29
description: Strasbourg have lost each of their last three matches against Nice in Ligue 1, after losing only two of the previous 11 since their return to the top-flight in the summer of 2017. Strasbourg have won their last five Ligue 1 games and could win six in a row in the same season in the top-flight for the second time in their history, having managed to do so between January and March 1935.

title: Saint-Étienne vs Brest - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 29
description: This will be the 30th game between St Etienne and Brest in Ligue 1. ASSE have lost five of the most recent six, which is as many as in the first 23. St Etienne have lost only one of their 14 home games against Brest in Ligue 1, in April 2021.

title: Auxerre vs Olympique Lyonnais - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 29
description: Auxerre have lost 47.3% of their matches against Lyon in Ligue 1, their highest losing percentage against an opponent that they have faced at least 10 times. Auxerre have won 10 matches in Ligue 1 this season, their highest total in a single campaign since 2010-11. In their previous season in the top-flight, AJA had half as many wins after 28 games.

title: Le Havre vs Rennes - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 29
description: Le Havre have won only two of their last 17 matches against Rennes in Ligue 1, and none of the three played since their return to the top-flight in the summer of 2023.
